iPod Touch 2G (iPod) Touch is a smartphone that was released in October 2010. The iPod Touch is a 7" touch screen device that is based on the iPod nano, but has a larger screen and a better built-in camera and video player (the first iPod with both features). It features a quad-core processor, A5 processor, 1 GB RAM, 8 GB storage, MicroSD card slot for expansion up to 32 GB. The iPod Touch is also the world's first Android phone/tablet hybrid device as it comes equipped with an Android operating system.

iPod Touch 2G (iPod Touch) has been launched in the market in two different versions. iPhone-version of iPod Touch 2G contains 1GB RAM (128 MB) processor (4 cores), 256 MB RAM (512 MB) storage, 8 GB storage capacity, A5 processor with VGA front-end, 1 GB RAM, microSD Card Slot for Expansion up to 32GB, Bluetooth, WiFi, 3G network. iPhone-version iPod Touch 2G costs about $200 and features the same basic hardware, and also includes Apple iChat service. However, iPhone version iPod Touch 2G will offer new features like iMessage, more than 100 new apps, new design, 3D graphics, a bigger screen, a bigger touch keyboard and an improved camera and video player. This is not the case with iPod Touch 1G version, which costs less than $100 and does not feature any of these new features.

iPod Touch 2G (iPod Touch) are available in two versions: 64MB iPod Touch 2G, 16GB iPod Touch 2G and 16GB iPod Touch 2G Plus. Both are identical to each other. The iPod Touch 2G is similar to the iPod Touch, but with a larger screen size, faster processor, more RAM and greater storage capacity. If you need a newer model with larger display, then you can buy an iPod Touch 2G (iPod Touch) 128MB, for about $250 or a 1GB iPod Touch 2G 64MB for $150. iPod Touch 2G 64MB also come with a 1 GB memory card slot for expansion.
